    {"question_text": "What is the output?\n\nclass MetricsWindow:\n    def __init__(self, size=10):\n        self.window = []\n        self.size = size\n    def record(self, success):\n        self.window.append(success)\n        if len(self.window) > self.size: self.window.pop(0)\n    def error_rate(self):\n        if not self.window: return 0.0\n        failures = self.window.count(False)\n        return failures / len(self.window)\n    def should_trip(self, threshold=0.26):\n        return self.error_rate() > threshold\n\nmw = MetricsWindow()\nfor _ in range(7): mw.record(True)\nfor _ in range(3): mw.record(False)\nprint(round(mw.error_rate(), 2), mw.should_trip())", "correct_answer": "A", "difficulty": "advanced", "topic": "system_design", "option_a": "0.3 True", "option_b": "0.3 False", "option_c": "0.7 True", "option_d": "0.0 False"},
